{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848553391,"sessionID":"ses_2872db2faffeLYLtEnCArhsJXh","part":{"id":"prt_d78d277a5001QBdEyxEvA8wzUl","messageID":"msg_d78d25d270010i7oyeS38selIk","sessionID":"ses_2872db2faffeLYLtEnCArhsJXh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_646b0faf299f42f884a3df82","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-010\n4: - **Module**: `pkg/router`\n5: - **Language**: Go\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: Draft\n8: \n9: ## 1. 概述\n10: \n11: `pkg/router` 是 agentcube 的 HTTP 反向代理核心模块，负责将外部 HTTP 请求路由到后端的 AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter 实例。本设计文档聚焦于**会话管理**（Session Management）功能，基于已有的反向代理能力，增加对会话生命周期、状态追踪、JWT 认证和动态服务发现的支持。\n12: \n13: ### 1.1 目标\n14: \n15: - 实现基于 Kubernetes CRD 的动态后端服务发现\n16: - 支持会话生命周期管理（创建、更新、销毁）\n17: - 提供 JWT 令牌认证和授权\n18: - 集成 client-go 进行 Kubernetes API 交互\n19: - 提供可观测性（Prometheus 指标、健康检查）\n20: \n21: ### 1.2 依赖\n22: \n23: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` — Kubernetes typed client\n24: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/informers` — Shared informer\n25: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/listers` — Resource listers\n26: - `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` — Kubernetes clientset\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## 2. 架构设计\n31: \n32: ### 2.1 整体架构\n33: \n34: ```\n35: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n36: │                            Client Requests                               │\n37: └─────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘\n38:                                   │\n39:                                   ▼\n40: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n41: │                         Router Server (pkg/router)                       │\n42: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐    │\n43: │  │  Auth       │→ │  Rate Limit │→ │  Route      │→ │   Proxy     │    │\n44: │  │  Middleware │  │  Middleware  │  │  Handler    │  │   Handler   │    │\n45: │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘    │\n46: │         │                 │                │                │           │\n47: │  ┌──────▼─────────────────▼────────────────▼────────────────▼──────┐   │\n48: │  │                     Backend Pool Manager                         │   │\n49: │  └────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n50: └───────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┘\n51:                                 │\n52:         ┌───────────────────────┼───────────────────────┐\n53:         │                       │                       │\n54:         ▼                       ▼                       ▼\n55: ┌───────────────┐      ┌─────────────────┐     ┌────────────────┐\n56: │   Health      │      │   Kubernetes    │     │    Metrics     │\n57: │   Checker     │      │   Informer      │     │    Collector   │\n58: └───────────────┘      └────────┬────────┘     └────────────────┘\n59:                                 │\n60:                                 ▼\n61:                  ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n62:                  │   Kubernetes API Server    │\n63:                  │  ┌─────────────────────┐  │\n64:                  │  │ AgentRuntime CRs     │  │\n65:                  │  │ CodeInterpreter CRs │  │\n66:                  │  └─────────────────────┘  │\n67:                  └─────────────────────────────┘\n68: ```\n69: \n70: ### 2.2 核心组件\n71: \n72: | 组件 | 职责 |\n73: |------|------|\n74: | `Router` | HTTP 服务器生命周期管理、主路由入口 |\n75: | `BackendPool` | 后端服务实例池管理、健康状态追踪 |\n76: | `RouteHandler` | 请求路径解析与目标后端选择 |\n77: | `ProxyHandler` | HTTP/WebSocket 请求转发 |\n78: | `HealthChecker` | 后端健康检查、故障检测 |\n79: | `Informer` | Kubernetes CRD 监听、动态服务发现 |\n80: | `Authenticator` | JWT/Bearer Token 认证 |\n81: | `RateLimiter` | 请求速率限制 |\n82: | `Metrics` | Prometheus 指标采集 |\n83: \n84: ### 2.3 数据流\n85: \n86: ```\n87: 1. 客户端请求进入 Router\n88:    │\n89: 2. Authenticator 验证认证信息 (JWT/Bearer)\n90:    │\n91: 3. RateLimiter 检查速率限制\n92:    │\n93: 4. RouteHandler 解析路径，提取 namespace/resource\n94:    │\n95: 5. BackendPool 根据路径/Header 选择目标后端\n96:    │\n97: 6. HealthChecker 检查后端健康状态\n98:    │\n99: 7. ProxyHandler 转发请求到后端\n100:    │\n101: 8. Metrics 记录请求指标\n102:    │\n103: 9. 响应返回客户端\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## 3. 数据结构\n109: \n110: ### 3.1 核心配置\n111: \n112: ```go\n113: // Config holds router configuration\n114: type Config struct {\n115:     // Server settings\n116:     ListenAddress       string        // Listen address (default: \":8080\")\n117:     BackendTimeout      time.Duration // Backend request timeout (default: 30s)\n118:     IdleTimeout         time.Duration // Idle connection timeout (default: 60s)\n119: \n120:     // Health check settings\n121:     HealthCheckInterval time.Duration // Health check interval (default: 10s)\n122:     HealthCheckTimeout  time.Duration // Health check timeout (default: 5s)\n123:     MaxFailures        int           // Max consecutive failures before marking unhealthy (default: 3)\n124: \n125:     // Connection pool settings\n126:     MaxConnsPerBackend  int           // Max connections per backend (default: 100)\n127: \n128:     // Rate limiting\n129:     RateLimitEnabled    bool          // Enable rate limiting (default: false)\n130:     RateLimitRPS        int           // Requests per second (default: 10)\n131:     RateLimitBurst      int           // Burst size (default: 20)\n132: \n133:     // Authentication\n134:     AuthEnabled         bool          // Enable authentication (default: false)\n135:     AuthToken           string        // Bearer token for auth\n136: \n137:     // Kubernetes integration\n138:     WatchNamespaces     []string      // Namespaces to watch (empty = all)\n139:     KubeConfigPath      string        // Path to kubeconfig (optional)\n140:     ResyncPeriod        time.Duration // Informer resync period (default: 30m)\n141: \n142:     // JWT settings\n143:     JWTEnabled         bool          // Enable JWT authentication (default: false)\n144:     JWTSecretName      string        // Kubernetes Secret name for JWT keys (default: \"agentcube-router-identity\")\n145:     JWTNamespace       string        // Secret namespace (default: \"default\")\n146:     JWTExpiration      time.Duration // Token expiration (default: 5m)\n147: }\n148: ```\n149: \n150: ### 3.2 后端服务\n151: \n152: ```go\n153: // Backend represents a backend service instance\n154: type Backend struct {\n155:     URL                 *url.URL      // Backend URL\n156:     PathPrefix          string        // Path prefix for routing\n157:     Name                string        // Backend name (for logging/metrics)\n158:     Healthy             bool          // Current health status\n159:     ConsecutiveFailures int           // Consecutive failure count\n160:     LastHealthyCheck    time.Time     // Last health check timestamp\n161:    mu                  sync.RWMutex   // Mutex for concurrent access\n162: }\n163: \n164: // BackendPool manages multiple backend instances\n165: type BackendPool struct {\n166:     backends     map[string]*Backend   // key: \"agentruntime/namespace/name\" or \"codeinterpreter/namespace/name\"\n167:     headerRoutes map[string]map[string]string // header-based routing rules\n168:     defaultBackend string               // Default fallback backend\n169:     mu           sync.RWMutex\n170: }\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ### 3.3 代理上下文\n174: \n175: ```go\n176: // ProxyContext holds request context for proxying\n177: type ProxyContext struct {\n178:     Context     context.Context\n179:     Request     *http.Request\n180:     Response    http.ResponseWriter\n181:     Backend     *Backend\n182:     StartTime   time.Time\n183:     RequestID   string\n184:     Namespace   string\n185:     ResourceName string\n186:     ResourceKind string // \"agentruntime\" or \"codeinterpreter\"\n187: }\n188: ```\n189: \n190: ### 3.4 会话管理\n191: \n192: ```go\n193: // SessionInfo represents session state\n194: type SessionInfo struct {\n195:     SessionID     string            // Unique session identifier\n196:     Namespace     string            // Kubernetes namespace\n197:     ResourceName  string            // AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter name\n198:     ResourceKind  string            // \"agentruntime\" or \"codeinterpreter\"\n199:     Endpoint      string            // Backend endpoint URL\n200:     CreatedAt     time.Time         // Session creation time\n201:     LastActivity  time.Time         // Last activity timestamp\n202:     ExpiresAt     time.Time         // Session expiration time\n203:     Labels        map[string]string // Labels from CR\n204:     Status        SessionStatus     // Current status\n205: }\n206: \n207: // SessionStatus enum\n208: type SessionStatus string\n209: \n210: const (\n211:     SessionStatusPending   SessionStatus = \"Pending\"\n212:     SessionStatusActive   SessionStatus = \"Active\"\n213:     SessionStatusIdle     SessionStatus = \"Idle\"\n214:     SessionStatusExpired  SessionStatus = \"Expired\"\n215:     SessionStatusFailed   SessionStatus = \"Failed\"\n216: )\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### 3.5 JWT 管理\n220: \n221: ```go\n222: // JWTManager handles JWT token generation and validation\n223: type JWTManager struct {\n224:     privateKey     *rsa.PrivateKey\n225:     publicKey     *rsa.PublicKey\n226:     clientset     kubernetes.Interface\n227:     secretName    string\n228:     secretNamespace string\n229:     expiration    time.Duration\n230: }\n231: \n232: // JWT claims structure\n233: type JWTClaims struct {\n234:     SessionID    string `json:\"session_id\"`\n235:     Namespace    string `json:\"namespace\"`\n236:     ResourceName string `json:\"resource_name\"`\n237:     ResourceKind string `json:\"resource_kind\"`\n238:     ExpiresAt    int64  `json:\"exp\"`\n239:     IssuedAt     int64  `json:\"iat\"`\n240:     Issuer       string `json:\"iss\"`\n241: }\n242: ```\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ## 4. API 合约\n247: \n248: ### 4.1 HTTP 端点\n249: \n250: | Method | Path | Middleware | Handler |\n251: |--------|------|------------|---------|\n252: | GET | `/health/live` | none | `handleHealthLive` |\n253: | GET | `/health/ready` | none | `handleHealthReady` |\n254: | GET | `/metrics` | none | Prometheus metrics |\n255: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/*path` | auth, rateLimit, log | `handleAgentRuntimeProxy` |\n256: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/*path` | auth, rateLimit, log | `handleAgentRuntimeProxy` |\n257: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/*path` | auth, rateLimit, log | `handleCodeInterpreterProxy` |\n258: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/*path` | auth, rateLimit, log | `handleCodeInterpreterProxy` |\n259: | WS | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/ws` | auth, rateLimit, log | `handleAgentRuntimeWS` |\n260: | WS | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/ws` | auth, rateLimit, log | `handleCodeInterpreterWS` |\n261: \n262: ### 4.2 代理请求头\n263: \n264: | Header | 描述 |\n265: |--------|------|\n266: | `X-Request-ID` | 请求唯一标识 |\n267: | `X-Forwarded-For` | 原始客户端 IP |\n268: | `X-Forwarded-Proto` | 原始协议 (http/https) |\n269: | `X-Real-IP` | 真实客户端 IP |\n270: | `X-Target-Namespace` | 目标 Kubernetes 命名空间 |\n271: | `X-Target-Name` | 目标资源名称 |\n272: | `X-Target-Kind` | 目标资源类型 (agentruntime/codeinterpreter) |\n273: | `X-Session-ID` | 会话标识 (JWT token 中的 session_id) |\n274: \n275: ### 4.3 健康检查响应\n276: \n277: ```go\n278: // Live check\n279: {\"status\": \"alive\"}\n280: \n281: // Ready check - OK\n282: {\"status\": \"ready\"}\n283: \n284: // Ready check - Not ready\n285: {\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"informers not synced\"}\n286: \n287: // Metrics endpoint\n288: # Prometheus metrics format\n289: ```\n290: \n291: ### 4.4 错误响应\n292: \n293: ```json\n294: {\n295:   \"error\": \"error message\",\n296:   \"code\": \"ERR_CODE\",\n297:   \"requestId\": \"req-xxx\"\n298: }\n299: ```\n300: \n301: | Status Code | Description |\n302: |-------------|-------------|\n303: | 200 | Success |\n304: | 400 | Bad Request (invalid path/params) |\n305: | 401 | Unauthorized (invalid/missing token) |\n306: | 404 | Resource not found |\n307: | 429 | Too Many Requests (rate limit) |\n308: | 502 | Bad Gateway (backend error) |\n309: | 503 | Service Unavailable (circuit open/overloaded) |\n310: | 504 | Gateway Timeout (backend timeout) |\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## 5. Kubernetes 集成\n315: \n316: ### 5.1 Informer 配置\n317: \n318: ```go\n319: // NewSharedInformerFactory creates informer factory\n320: func NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, resyncPeriod time.Duration) externalversions.SharedInformerFactory\n321: \n322: // Watch AgentRuntime resources\n323: factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()\n324: \n325: // Watch CodeInterpreter resources\n326: factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()\n327: ```\n328: \n329: ### 5.2 事件处理\n330: \n331: ```go\n332: // AgentRuntime event handlers\n333: func (i *Informer) AddAgentRuntime(obj *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n334: func (i *Informer) UpdateAgentRuntime(oldObj, newObj *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n335: func (i *Informer) DeleteAgentRuntime(obj *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n336: \n337: // CodeInterpreter event handlers\n338: func (i *Informer) AddCodeInterpreter(obj *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n339: func (i *Informer) UpdateCodeInterpreter(oldObj, newObj *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n340: func (i *Informer) DeleteCodeInterpreter(obj *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n341: ```\n342: \n343: ### 5.3 后端注册逻辑\n344: \n345: ```\n346: AddAgentRuntime:\n347:   1. 检查 Status.Phase == \"Running\"\n348:   2. 检查 Status.Endpoint != \"\"\n349:   3. 构造 backend key: \"agentruntime/{namespace}/{name}\"\n350:   4. 从 Spec.TargetPorts 提取 PathPrefix (默认 \"/agent/\")\n351:   5. 调用 BackendPool.AddBackend()\n352: \n353: UpdateAgentRuntime:\n354:   1. 如果不再 Running 或无 Endpoint，调用 RemoveBackend()\n355:   2. 否则调用 BackendPool.UpdateBackend()\n356: \n357: DeleteAgentRuntime:\n358:   1. 调用 RemoveBackend()\n359: ```\n360: \n361: ---\n362: \n363: ## 6. 错误处理\n364: \n365: ### 6.1 错误类型\n366: \n367: ```go\n368: // Error codes\n369: const (\n370:     ErrCodeBadRequest       = \"ERR_BAD_REQUEST\"\n371:     ErrCodeNotFound         = \"ERR_NOT_FOUND\"\n372:     ErrCodeUnauthorized     = \"ERR_UNAUTHORIZED\"\n373:     ErrCodeTargetNotReady   = \"ERR_TARGET_NOT_READY\"\n374:     ErrCodeProxyFailed      = \"ERR_PROXY_FAILED\"\n375:     ErrCodeTimeout          = \"ERR_TIMEOUT\"\n376:     ErrCodeCircuitOpen      = \"ERR_CIRCUIT_OPEN\"\n377:     ErrCodeRateLimited      = \"ERR_RATE_LIMITED\"\n378:     ErrCodeInternalError    = \"ERR_INTERNAL\"\n379: )\n380: \n381: // RouterError represents a router-specific error\n382: type RouterError struct {\n383:     Code       string\n384:     Message    string\n385:     StatusCode int\n386:     Err        error\n387: }\n388: ```\n389: \n390: ### 6.2 错误处理策略\n391: \n392: | 错误场景 | 处理策略 |\n393: |----------|----------|\n394: | 认证失败 | 返回 401，记录错误指标 |\n395: | 资源不存在 (404) | 返回 404，不重试 |\n396: | 速率超限 | 返回 429，提示客户端退避 |\n397: | 后端超时 | 记录失败，重试一次，失败则熔断 |\n398: | 后端连接失败 | 熔断计数，达到阈值后标记不健康 |\n399: | 熔断器开启 | 返回 503，定期尝试恢复 |\n400: | 内部错误 | 返回 500，记录错误日志 |\n401: \n402: ### 6.3 日志规范\n403: \n404: ```go\n405: // Structured logging with fields\n406: log.Info(\"Request processed\",\n407:     \"requestId\", requestID,\n408:     \"method\", method,\n409:     \"path\", path,\n410:     \"namespace\", namespace,\n411:     \"resourceName\", resourceName,\n412:     \"backend\", backendName,\n413:     \"latency\", latency,\n414:     \"statusCode\", statusCode,\n415: )\n416: ```\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: ## 7. 测试策略\n421: \n422: ### 7.1 单元测试\n423: \n424: | 模块 | 测试重点 |\n425: |------|----------|\n426: | `BackendPool` | 并发安全、路由选择、健康状态管理 |\n427: | `RouteHandler` | 路径解析、Header 路由、后端选择 |\n428: | `ProxyHandler` | URL 重写、Header 设置、连接池管理 |\n429: | `HealthChecker` | 健康检查触发、状态转换、失败计数 |\n430: | `Authenticator` | Token 验证、Middleware 流程 |\n431: | `RateLimiter` | 速率限制、并发安全、Middleware 流程 |\n432: | `Metrics` | 指标记录、标签正确性 |\n433: \n434: ### 7.2 集成测试\n435: \n436: ```go\n437: // 使用 fake client-go 进行集成测试\n438: import (\n439:     \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n440:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/fake\"\n441: )\n442: \n443: func TestRouterWithFakeClients(t *testing.T) {\n444:     // Setup fake clients\n445:     kubeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n446:     runtimeClient := clientsetfake.NewSimpleClientset()\n447: \n448:     // Create informer factory\n449:     informerFactory := externalversions.NewSharedInformerFactory(runtimeClient, 30*time.Minute)\n450: \n451:     // Create router with fake clients\n452:     router := NewRouter(&Config{\n453:         WatchNamespaces: []string{\"default\"},\n454:     })\n455: \n456:     // Add test AgentRuntime\n457:     ar := &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n458:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n459:             Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n460:             Namespace: \"default\",\n461:         },\n462:         Status: agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n463:             Phase:    agentcubev1alpha1.PhaseRunning,\n464:             Endpoint: \"http://localhost:8081\",\n465:         },\n466:     }\n467:     runtimeClient.AgentRuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(context.Background(), ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n468: \n469:     // Start informers\n470:     informerFactory.Start(nil)\n471:     informerFactory.WaitForCacheSync(nil)\n472: \n473:     // Test proxy flow\n474:     req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/test-runtime/api\", nil)\n475:     w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n476:     router.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n477: \n478:     assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, w.Code)\n479: }\n480: ```\n481: \n482: ### 7.3 测试场景\n483: \n484: | 场景 | 预期结果 |\n485: |------|----------|\n486: | 正常代理流程 | 请求成功转发，后端响应正确返回 |\n487: | 后端动态添加 | Informer 事件触发，后端自动加入路由 |\n488: | 后端动态删除 | Informer 事件触发，后端从路由移除 |\n489: | 健康检查失败 | 连续失败 3 次后标记为不健康，流量切换 |\n490: | 认证失败 | 返回 401，请求不转发 |\n491: | 速率超限 | 返回 429，请求不转发 |\n492: | 后端超时 | 重试一次，失败返回 504 |\n493: | WebSocket 连接 | 长连接保持，双向通信正常 |\n494: \n495: ### 7.4 测试覆盖率目标\n496: \n497: | 组件 | 目标覆盖率 |\n498: |------|-----------|\n499: | server.go | 80% |\n500: | backend.go | 85% |\n501: | route.go | 85% |\n502: | proxy.go | 80% |\n503: | health.go | 85% |\n504: | informer.go | 80% |\n505: | auth.go | 90% |\n506: | ratelimit.go | 90% |\n507: | metrics.go | 85% |\n508: \n509: ---\n510: \n511: ## 8. 关键接口定义\n512: \n513: ### 8.1 Router 接口\n514: \n515: ```go\n516: type Router interface {\n517:     // Start begins serving HTTP requests\n518:     Start() error\n519: \n520:     // Stop gracefully shuts down the router\n521:     Stop(ctx context.Context) error\n522: \n523:     // AddBackend adds a backend to the pool\n524:     AddBackend(key, endpoint, pathPrefix, name string) error\n525: \n526:     // RemoveBackend removes a backend from the pool\n527:     RemoveBackend(key string)\n528: \n529:     // GetConfig returns current configuration\n530:     GetConfig() *Config\n531: \n532:     // GetMetrics returns current metrics\n533:     GetMetrics() *Metrics\n534: }\n535: ```\n536: \n537: ### 8.2 ServiceDiscoverer 接口\n538: \n539: ```go\n540: type ServiceDiscoverer interface {\n541:     // Start starts the informer\n542:     Start() error\n543: \n544:     // Stop stops the informer\n545:     Stop()\n546: \n547:     // GetEndpoint returns endpoint for given namespace and name\n548:     GetEndpoint(namespace, name, kind string) (string, error)\n549: }\n550: ```\n551: \n552: ### 8.3 ProxyHandler 接口\n553: \n554: ```go\n555: type ProxyHandler interface {\n556:     // ServeHTTP proxies the request to backend\n557:     ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request, backend *Backend)\n558: \n559:     // GetTransport returns the underlying HTTP transport\n560:     GetTransport() *http.Transport\n561: }\n562: ```\n563: \n564: ---\n565: \n566: ## 9. 监控指标\n567: \n568: ### 9.1 Prometheus 指标\n569: \n570: | Metric | Type | Labels | Description |\n571: |--------|------|--------|-------------|\n572: | `router_request_duration_seconds` | Histogram | method, path, backend | Request duration |\n573: | `router_backend_requests_total` | Counter | backend, status | Backend request count |\n574: | `router_backend_healthy` | Gauge | backend | Backend health status (1/0) |\n575: | `router_errors_total` | Counter | type | Error count by type |\n576: | `router_rate_limit_rejected_total` | Counter | client_ip | Rate limited requests |\n577: | `router_active_connections` | Gauge | backend | Active connections per backend |\n578: | `router_informer_sync_total` | Counter | resource_type | Informer sync count |\n579: \n580: ### 9.2 健康检查端点\n581: \n582: - `/health/live` — Liveness probe (always returns 200 if process is running)\n583: - `/health/ready` — Readiness probe (returns 200 only if informers are synced and backend pool is initialized)\n584: \n585: ---\n586: \n587: ## 10. 实施计划\n588: \n589: ### Phase 1: 核心功能\n590: - [ ] 完善 Router 主结构\n591: - [ ] 实现 BackendPool 的线程安全操作\n592: - [ ] 实现基础代理转发\n593: \n594: ### Phase 2: Kubernetes 集成\n595: - [ ] 实现 Informer 完整功能\n596: - [ ] 集成 client-go 进行 CRD 监听\n597: - [ ] 实现 Add/Update/Delete 事件处理\n598: \n599: ### Phase 3: 会话管理\n600: - [ ] 实现 JWT Token 生成和验证\n601: - [ ] 实现会话状态追踪\n602: - [ ] 实现基于 session 的路由\n603: \n604: ### Phase 4: 可靠性\n605: - [ ] 完善健康检查逻辑\n606: - [ ] 实现熔断机制\n607: - [ ] 添加超时控制\n608: \n609: ### Phase 5: 可观测性\n610: - [ ] 完善日志结构化\n611: - [ ] 添加完整 Prometheus 指标\n612: - [ ] 实现健康检查端点\n613: \n614: ---\n615: \n616: ## 11. 依赖\n617: \n618: ### 11.1 外部依赖\n619: \n620: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n621: |---------|---------|---------|\n622: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | ^1.9.0 | HTTP framework |\n623: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | ^5.0.0 | JWT token handling |\n624: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` | ^1.16.0 | Metrics |\n625: | `golang.org/x/time/rate` | ^0.5.0 | Rate limiting |\n626: | `k8s.io/client-go` | ^0.34.0 | Kubernetes client |\n627: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | ^0.34.0 | API types |\n628: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | ^2.100.0 | Logging |\n629: \n630: ### 11.2 内部依赖\n631: \n632: | Module | Purpose |\n633: |--------|---------|\n634: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated Kubernetes typed client |\n635: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | CRD types |\n636: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/listers` | Resource listers |\n637: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/informers` | Shared informers |\n638: \n639: ---\n640: \n641: ## 12. 参考\n642: \n643: - [AR-009: Router HTTP 反向代理核心](design.md)\n644: - [Session Routing Design](session-routing/design.md)\n645: - [client-go library](deployment/client-go.md)\n646: - [Kubernetes Informer Pattern](https://medium.com/@cloud_eng/kubernetes-informers-the-magic-behind-operator-frameworks-2c4e3a87a9c3)\n\n(End of file - total 646 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-010\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Draft\n\n## 1. 概述\n\n`pkg/router` 是 agentcube 的 HTTP 反向代理核心模块，负责将外部 HTTP 请求路由到后端的 AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter 实例。本设计文档聚焦于**会话管理**（Session Management）功能，基于已有的反向代理能力，增加对会话生命周期、状态追踪、JWT 认证和动态服务发现的支持。\n\n### 1.1 目标\n\n- 实现基于 Kubernetes CRD 的动态后端服务发现\n- 支持会话生命周期管理（创建、更新、销毁）\n- 提供 JWT 令牌认证和授权\n- 集成 client-go 进行 Kubernetes API 交互\n- 提供可观测性（Prometheus 指标、健康检查）\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/design.md","time":{"start":1775848553369,"end":1775848553389}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848553394,"sessionID":"ses_2872db2faffeLYLtEnCArhsJXh","part":{"id":"prt_d78d272ae001LrwRkcjxcKy2SC","messageID":"msg_d78d25d270010i7oyeS38selIk","sessionID":"ses_2872db2faffeLYLtEnCArhsJXh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0bf8772806f649239aa196a2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session management in `pkg/router`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-010\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/router`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The router module requires session management to maintain stateful connections and track client sessions to backend services. This enables sticky sessions, session affinity, lifecycle management, and operational visibility into active sessions.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirement: Session Configuration\n23: \n24: ### Scenario: Router creates session store with default configuration\n25: \n26: **GIVEN** a Router instance is created with `sessionEnabled: true` and no explicit session configuration\n27: **WHEN** the router initializes\n28: **THEN** it SHOULD use default values: session timeout `30m`, cookie name `\"AGENTSESSIONID\"`, max active sessions `10000`, cleanup interval `5m`\n29: \n30: ### Scenario: Router creates session store with custom configuration\n31: \n32: **GIVEN** a Router instance is created with session configuration: `sessionTimeout: \"60m\"`, `sessionCookieName: \"SID\"`, `sessionMaxActive: 5000`\n33: **WHEN** the router initializes\n34: **THEN** it SHOULD configure session timeout to 60 minutes, cookie name to \"SID\", and limit to 5000 concurrent sessions\n35: \n36: ### Scenario: Router disables session management\n37: \n38: **GIVEN** a Router instance with `sessionEnabled: false` (default)\n39: **WHEN** HTTP requests are received\n40: **THEN** the router SHOULD NOT track sessions\n41: **AND** no session cookies SHOULD be set\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Requirement: Session ID Generation\n46: \n47: ### Scenario: Router generates unique session ID for new session\n48: \n49: **GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n50: **WHEN** a new client connects without a session ID\n51: **THEN** the router SHOULD generate a unique session ID\n52: **AND** the session ID SHOULD be a valid UUID v4 format\n53: \n54: ### Scenario: Router generates unique session IDs without collision\n55: \n56: **GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n57: **WHEN** 1000 new clients connect simultaneously without session IDs\n58: **THEN** the router SHOULD generate 1000 unique session IDs\n59: **AND** no two sessions SHOULD share the same ID\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## Requirement: Session Storage\n64: \n65: ### Scenario: Router stores session data\n66: \n67: **GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n68: **WHEN** a new session is created with session ID \"uuid-123\"\n69: **THEN** the session SHOULD store: ID, backend reference, start time, last activity time, metadata\n70: **AND** the session SHOULD be retrievable by session ID\n71: \n72: ### Scenario: Router retrieves existing session\n73: \n74: **GIVEN** a Router with active sessions in the store\n75: **WHEN** a client reconnects with a valid session ID\n76: **THEN** the router SHOULD restore the complete session state\n77: **AND** the session's last activity time SHOULD be updated\n78: \n79: ### Scenario: Router returns nil for invalid session ID\n80: \n81: **GIVEN** a Router with active sessions\n82: **WHEN** a client connects with a non-existent session ID \"invalid-uuid\"\n83: **THEN** the router SHOULD return nil (no session found)\n84: **AND** the request SHOULD be treated as a new session\n85: \n86: ### Scenario: Session store enforces max session limit\n87: \n88: **GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled and `sessionMaxActive: 100`\n89: **AND** 100 active sessions exist in the store\n90: **WHEN** a 101st new session is requested\n91: **THEN** the router SHOULD reject the new session creation\n92: **OR** evict an expired session to make room\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Requirement: Session Middleware\n97: \n98: ### Scenario: Session middleware extracts session from cookie\n99: \n100: **GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n101: **WHEN** an HTTP request arrives with cookie `AGENTSESSIONID=valid-uuid`\n102: **THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the session ID\n103: **AND** load the corresponding session from the store\n104: \n105: ### Scenario: Session middleware extracts session from header\n106: \n107: **GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n108: **WHEN** an HTTP request arrives with header `X-Session-ID: valid-uuid` and no cookie\n109: **THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the session ID from the header\n110: **AND** load the corresponding session from the store\n111: \n112: ### Scenario: Session middleware creates new session for first request\n113: \n114: **GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n115: **WHEN** an HTTP request arrives without session cookie or header\n116: **THEN** the middleware SHOULD create a new session\n117: **AND** set response cookie `AGENTSESSIONID` with the generated session ID\n118: \n119: ### Scenario: Session middleware updates last activity on request\n120: \n121: **GIVEN** an active session with last activity time T0\n122: **WHEN** a request arrives with valid session ID\n123: **THEN** the session's last activity time SHOULD be updated to current time T1\n124: **AND** T1 SHOULD be greater than T0\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## Requirement: Session Affinity (Sticky Sessions)\n129: \n130: ### Scenario: Router routes request to session's assigned backend\n131: \n132: **GIVEN** a session with backend \"backend-key-1\" stored in session data\n133: **WHEN** a request arrives with the session's ID\n134: **THEN** the router SHOULD route the request to backend \"backend-key-1\"\n135: **AND** NOT perform load balancing across backends\n136: \n137: ### Scenario: Router creates new session with backend assignment\n138: \n139: **GIVEN** a Router with session management and backend pool containing backends\n140: **WHEN** a new session is created for a request routed to \"backend-2\"\n141: **THEN** the session SHOULD store \"backend-2\" as its assigned backend\n142: **AND** future requests with this session SHOULD route to \"backend-2\"\n143: \n144: ### Scenario: Router handles session when backend is removed\n145: \n146: **GIVEN** a session with backend \"removed-backend\" stored\n147: **WHEN** the \"removed-backend\" is removed from the backend pool\n148: **THEN** the session SHOULD be invalidated\n149: **OR** the session SHOULD be reassigned to a new valid backend\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## Requirement: Session Lifecycle - Expiration\n154: \n155: ### Scenario: Session expires after timeout\n156: \n157: **GIVEN** a session created at time T0 with timeout 30 minutes\n158: **WHEN** the current time exceeds T0 + 30 minutes\n159: **THEN** the session SHOULD be marked as expired\n160: **AND** subsequent requests with this session ID SHOULD be rejected\n161: \n162: ### Scenario: Session expiration resets on activity\n163: \n164: **GIVEN** a session created at T0 with timeout 30 minutes\n165: **WHEN** a request arrives at T0 + 25 minutes\n166: **THEN** the session expiration SHOULD be extended to T0 + 25 + 30 minutes\n167: **AND** the session SHOULD remain valid\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Requirement: Session Lifecycle - Cleanup\n172: \n173: ### Scenario: Router runs periodic session cleanup\n174: \n175: **GIVEN** a Router with session cleanup interval set to 5 minutes\n176: **WHEN** the cleanup interval elapses\n177: **THEN** expired sessions SHOULD be removed from the store\n178: **AND** the active session count SHOULD decrease accordingly\n179: \n180: ### Scenario: Cleanup removes only expired sessions\n181: \n182: **GIVEN** a session store with 10 active sessions and 5 expired sessions\n183: **WHEN** session cleanup runs\n184: **THEN** only the 5 expired sessions SHOULD be removed\n185: **AND** the 10 active sessions SHOULD remain intact\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ## Requirement: Session Cookie Configuration\n190: \n191: ### Scenario: Router sets secure cookie flags\n192: \n193: **GIVEN** a Router with `sessionCookieSecure: true` and `sessionCookieHTTPOnly: true`\n194: **WHEN** a new session is created\n195: **THEN** the set cookie SHOULD include `Secure` flag\n196: **AND** the set cookie SHOULD include `HttpOnly` flag\n197: \n198: ### Scenario: Router sets cookie domain\n199: \n200: **GIVEN** a Router with `sessionCookieDomain: \"example.com\"`\n201: **WHEN** a new session is created\n202: **THEN** the set cookie SHOULD include `Domain=example.com`\n203: \n204: ### Scenario: Router sets cookie path\n205: \n206: **GIVEN** a Router with default configuration\n207: **WHEN** a new session is created\n208: **THEN** the set cookie SHOULD include `Path=/`\n209: \n210: ---\n211: \n212: ## Requirement: Session Metrics\n213: \n214: ### Scenario: Router exports active session count\n215: \n216: **GIVEN** a Router with session management and metrics enabled\n217: **WHEN** 50 active sessions exist\n218: **THEN** a Prometheus gauge `router_sessions_active` SHOULD report 50\n219: \n220: ### Scenario: Router tracks session creation rate\n221: \n222: **GIVEN** a Router with session management and metrics enabled\n223: **WHEN** new sessions are created\n224: **THEN** a Prometheus counter `router_sessions_created_total` SHOULD be incremented\n225: \n226: ### Scenario: Router tracks session expiration rate\n227: \n228: **GIVEN** a Router with session management and metrics enabled\n229: **WHEN** sessions expire and are cleaned up\n230: **THEN** a Prometheus counter `router_sessions_expired_total` SHOULD be incremented\n231: \n232: ### Scenario: Router exports session duration histogram\n233: \n234: **GIVEN** a Router with session management and metrics enabled\n235: **WHEN** a session expires\n236: **THEN** a Prometheus histogram `router_session_duration_seconds` SHOULD record the session lifetime\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## Requirement: Graceful Shutdown\n241: \n242: ### Scenario: Router closes session store on shutdown\n243: \n244: **GIVEN** a running Router with active sessions\n245: **WHEN** `Shutdown()` is called\n246: **THEN** the router SHOULD stop accepting new sessions\n247: **AND** existing sessions SHOULD remain available until cleanup\n248: \n249: ---\n250: \n251: ## Acceptance Criteria\n252: \n253: - [ ] Session IDs are generated uniquely (UUID v4)\n254: - [ ] Sessions persist across requests with same session ID\n255: - [ ] Session cookie is set on first request when enabled\n256: - [ ] Sticky sessions route to the same backend\n257: - [ ] Sessions expire after configured timeout\n258: - [ ] Expired sessions are cleaned up automatically\n259: - [ ] Session metrics are exported (active, created, expired)\n260: - [ ] Max session limit is enforced\n261: - [ ] Session data includes backend, start time, last activity\n262: - [ ] Cookie includes Secure and HttpOnly flags when configured\n263: - [ ] Session can be extracted from cookie or X-Session-ID header\n264: - [ ] Graceful shutdown completes without losing active session data\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ## References\n269: \n270: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md`\n271: - Proposal: `proposal.md`\n\n(End of file - total 271 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session management in `pkg/router`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-010\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe router module requires session management to maintain stateful connections and track client sessions to backend services. This enables sticky sessions, session affinity, lifecycle management, and operational visibility into active sessions.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775848553367,"end":1775848553392}}}}
