{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848559336,"sessionID":"ses_2872db2faffeLYLtEnCArhsJXh","part":{"id":"prt_d78d28e5e001tleWQK2AUKEXyN","messageID":"msg_d78d27be4001P3CT1mTO203lxP","sessionID":"ses_2872db2faffeLYLtEnCArhsJXh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_80df6cfbac494db9a16a42d5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/router  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Implementation)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Core Infrastructure\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Create `pkg/router/config.go` — Config struct with defaults (listen `:8080`, backend timeout `30s`, idle timeout `60s`, health check `10s`)\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/router/server.go` — Router struct with Start/Shutdown methods\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/router/backend.go` — Backend pool management (add/remove/update endpoints)\n15: - [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/router/proxy.go` — Reverse proxy implementation with httputil\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Phase 2: Kubernetes Informers\n20: \n21: - [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/router/informer.go` — Setup AgentRuntime informer with namespace filtering\n22: - [ ] **2.2** Create `pkg/router/informer.go` — Setup CodeInterpreter informer with namespace filtering\n23: - [ ] **2.3** Implement `addAgentRuntime()` handler — Add endpoint when AgentRuntime phase=Running\n24: - [ ] **2.4** Implement `updateAgentRuntime()` handler — Update endpoint on status change\n25: - [ ] **2.5** Implement `deleteAgentRuntime()` handler — Remove endpoint on CR deletion\n26: - [ ] **2.6** Implement `addCodeInterpreter()` handler — Add endpoint when CodeInterpreter phase=Running\n27: - [ ] **2.7** Implement `updateCodeInterpreter()` handler — Update endpoint on status change\n28: - [ ] **2.8** Implement `deleteCodeInterpreter()` handler — Remove endpoint on CR deletion\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ## Phase 3: Routing Logic\n33: \n34: - [ ] **3.1** Create `pkg/router/route.go` — Path prefix matching (e.g., `/agent/` → backend)\n35: - [ ] **3.2** Create `pkg/router/route.go` — Header-based routing (X-Backend, Content-Type)\n36: - [ ] **3.3** Implement 404 response for unmatched paths\n37: - [ ] **3.4** Implement query parameter preservation in routing\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## Phase 4: Health Checking\n42: \n43: - [ ] **4.1** Create `pkg/router/health.go` — Periodic health check scheduler\n44: - [ ] **4.2** Implement health check request with 5s timeout\n45: - [ ] **4.3** Implement unhealthy backend removal (3 consecutive failures)\n46: - [ ] **4.4** Implement backend recovery (mark healthy on success)\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Phase 5: Connection Pooling\n51: \n52: - [ ] **5.1** Configure httputil.ReverseProxy with Transport for keep-alive\n53: - [ ] **5.2** Implement max connections per backend limit (default 100)\n54: - [ ] **5.3** Implement idle connection cleanup (idleTimeout)\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Phase 6: Middleware\n59: \n60: - [ ] **6.1** Create `pkg/router/ratelimit.go` — Token bucket rate limiting (enable/disable)\n61: - [ ] **6.2** Create `pkg/router/auth.go` — Bearer token validation middleware\n62: - [ ] **6.3** Create `pkg/router/logging.go` — Request/response logging middleware\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ## Phase 7: Metrics\n67: \n68: - [ ] **7.1** Implement `router_request_duration_seconds` histogram\n69: - [ ] **7.2** Implement `router_backend_requests_total` counter\n70: - [ ] **7.3** Implement `router_backend_healthy` gauge\n71: - [ ] **7.4** Implement `router_errors_total` counter\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## Phase 8: Verification\n76: \n77: - [ ] **8.1** `go build ./pkg/router/...` — successful compilation\n78: - [ ] **8.2** `go test ./pkg/router/... -v` — all unit tests pass\n79: - [ ] **8.3** Integration test: Router starts, discovers CRs, routes requests\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## Dependencies\n84: \n85: - `k8s.io/client-go/informers` — Kubernetes informers\n86: - `k8s.io/client-go/listers` — CR listers\n87: - `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` — Metrics\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## References\n92: \n93: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md`\n\n(End of file - total 93 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/router  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Implementation)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Core Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Create `pkg/router/config.go` — Config struct with defaults (listen `:8080`, backend timeout `30s`, idle timeout `60s`, health check `10s`)\n- [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/router/server.go` — Router struct with Start/Shutdown methods\n- [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/router/backend.go` — Backend pool management (add/remove/update endpoints)\n- [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/router/proxy.go` — Reverse proxy implementation with httputil\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Kubernetes Informers\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775848559326,"end":1775848559334}}}}
