{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775848568538,"sessionID":"ses_2872db2faffeLYLtEnCArhsJXh","part":{"id":"prt_d78d2b6d900152Wwz6B5zZk797","messageID":"msg_d78d2aa3b001guE9wYV33p2mk3","sessionID":"ses_2872db2faffeLYLtEnCArhsJXh","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848595623,"sessionID":"ses_2872db2faffeLYLtEnCArhsJXh","part":{"id":"prt_d78d2c109001TCTcIfqeCrrHQj","messageID":"msg_d78d2aa3b001guE9wYV33p2mk3","sessionID":"ses_2872db2faffeLYLtEnCArhsJXh","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_784489d3028e4ad587e0aea0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/router  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Session Configuration\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Add session config fields to `Config` struct — `SessionEnabled`, `SessionTimeout`, `SessionCookieName`, `SessionMaxActive`, `SessionCookieSecure`, `SessionCookieHTTPOnly`, `SessionCookieDomain`\n- [ ] **1.2** Implement `DefaultConfig()` session defaults — timeout `30m`, cookie `\"AGENTSESSIONID\"`, max `10000`, cleanup `5m`\n- [ ] **1.3** Add session cleanup interval config — `SessionCleanupInterval` with default `5m`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Session Data Structures\n\n- [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/router/session.go` — `Session` struct with ID, Backend, CreatedAt, LastActivity, ExpiresAt, Metadata fields\n- [ ] **2.2** Create `pkg/router/session.go` — `SessionStore` interface (Create, Get, Update, Delete, List, Cleanup)\n- [ ] **2.3** Implement in-memory `MemorySessionStore` — thread-safe map with RWMutex\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Session ID Generation\n\n- [ ] **3.1** Implement `GenerateSessionID()` — return UUID v4 using `github.com/google/uuid`\n- [ ] **3.2** Write unit test: Generate 1000 IDs, verify all unique\n- [ ] **3.3** Write unit test: Verify UUID v4 format\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: Session Storage Operations\n\n- [ ] **4.1** Implement `SessionStore.Create()` — create session with generated ID, backend ref, timestamps\n- [ ] **4.2** Implement `SessionStore.Get()` — retrieve by session ID, return nil if not found\n- [ ] **4.3** Implement `SessionStore.Update()` — update last activity time\n- [ ] **4.4** Implement `SessionStore.Delete()` — remove session by ID\n- [ ] **4.5** Implement `SessionStore.List()` — return all active sessions\n- [ ] **4.6** Implement max session limit enforcement — reject new session when at limit\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Session Middleware\n\n- [ ] **5.1** Create `pkg/router/session_middleware.go` — extract session from cookie `AGENTSESSIONID`\n- [ ] **5.2** Create `pkg/router/session_middleware.go` — extract session from header `X-Session-ID`\n- [ ] **5.3** Create new session if none found — generate ID, set response cookie\n- [ ] **5.4** Update last activity on each request — extend expiration on activity\n- [ ] **5.5** Integrate middleware into router handler chain\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Session Expiration\n\n- [ ] **6.1** Implement session expiration check — mark expired based on `ExpiresAt`\n- [ ] **6.2** Implement sliding expiration — reset `ExpiresAt` on activity\n- [ ] **6.3** Reject requests with expired session — return new session\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Session Cleanup\n\n- [ ] **7.1** Implement periodic cleanup goroutine — run every cleanup interval\n- [ ] **7.2** Implement `Cleanup()` method — remove all expired sessions\n- [ ] **7.3** Add cleanup to router lifecycle — start on Start(), stop on Shutdown()\n- [ ] **7.4** Write unit test: Verify expired sessions are removed\n\n---\n\n## Phase 8: Session Affinity (Sticky Sessions)\n\n- [ ] **8.1** Store backend reference in session — on new session creation\n- [ ] **8.2** Route request to session's assigned backend — use stored backend key\n- [ ] **8.3** Handle backend removal — invalidate session when backend removed\n- [ ] **8.4** Write unit test: Verify same session routes to same backend\n\n---\n\n## Phase 9: Session Cookie Configuration\n\n- [ ] **9.1** Set cookie `Secure` flag — when `SessionCookieSecure: true`\n- [ ] **9.2** Set cookie `HttpOnly` flag — when `SessionCookieHTTPOnly: true`\n- [ ] **9.3** Set cookie `Domain` — when `SessionCookieDomain` configured\n- [ ] **9.4** Set cookie `Path` — default to `/`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 10: Session Metrics\n\n- [ ] **10.1** Add `router_sessions_active` gauge — track active session count\n- [ ] **10.2** Add `router_sessions_created_total` counter — track session creation\n- [ ] **10.3** Add `router_sessions_expired_total` counter — track expiration\n- [ ] **10.4** Add `router_session_duration_seconds` histogram — track session lifetime\n- [ ] **10.5** Update metrics on create/expire/cleanup events\n\n---\n\n## Phase 11: Graceful Shutdown\n\n- [ ] **11.1** Stop accepting new sessions on shutdown\n- [ ] **11.2** Wait for cleanup goroutine to finish\n- [ ] **11.3** Ensure existing sessions remain available during shutdown\n\n---\n\n## Phase 12: Verification\n\n- [ ] **12.1** `go build ./pkg/router/...` — successful compilation\n- [ ] **12.2** `go test ./pkg/router/... -v` — all unit tests pass\n- [ ] **12.3** Test: Default session config creates store with correct defaults\n- [ ] **12.4** Test: Custom session config overrides defaults\n- [ ] **12.5** Test: Session middleware extracts from cookie\n- [ ] **12.6** Test: Session middleware extracts from header\n- [ ] **12.7** Test: New session sets response cookie\n- [ ] **12.8** Test: Sticky session routes to same backend\n- [ ] **12.9** Test: Session expires after timeout\n- [ ] **12.10** Test: Cleanup removes expired sessions\n- [ ] **12.11** Test: Metrics reflect session state changes\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/google/uuid` — Session ID generation\n- `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` — Metrics\n- AR-009 (completed) — Router core infrastructure\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md`\n- Design: `pkg/router/design.md`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_2026